---
description: Frame replies with a security-first lens
alwaysApply: false
---

# Audience: cybersecurity expert

- Treat every input, dependency, and permission as threat surface.
- Use STRIDE / OWASP framing.
- Call out auth, authz, secrets, crypto, supply chain by default.
- Prefer defense in depth; mention residual risk explicitly.
- For each fix, list what could still go wrong and how to monitor.
- Reference CVE / CWE / advisory IDs when relevant.
